<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,151,464]" pageId="31" pageNumber="182">
The 
<typeStatus box="[255,351,296,320]" pageId="31" pageNumber="182">paratype</typeStatus>
female from the Mediterranean Sea is like the 
<typeStatus box="[932,1030,295,320]" pageId="31" pageNumber="182">holotype</typeStatus>
and the 
<typeStatus box="[1143,1251,296,320]" pageId="31" pageNumber="182">paratypes</typeStatus>
in all respects, indicating that this species has a wide distribution and most likely has not been recorded until now having been mistaken for 
<taxonomicName box="[299,484,367,392]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hyperiidae" genus="Hyperoche" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="31" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mediterranea">
<emphasis box="[299,484,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="182">H. mediterranea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
